name: Northern Virginia Community College
directions: In the Bisdorf building (AA), on NOVA's Alexandria campus, enter the front doors of the Bisdorf Building (this is the 2nd floor) stick to the right after entering both sets of doors (outside doors and doors right in front of you). Go passed the library and down the hallway, on the right, and walk down to The Academic Success Center (ASC), which is in Room 229. (AA 229). There is a single stall gender neutral all gender bathroom available inside of the Center.
comment:
You will most likely be asked at The Academic Success Center (ASC) why you are there, as they do tutoring there. Just tell them you are there to use the bathroom if asked your reason for coming to the Center. You may not be asked, but you often will be. This can seem intimidating, but they are just trying to make sure everyone who needs tutoring as a walk in or who have a tutoring appointment are seen by a tutor. They mean you no harm. It may be annoying to have to state why you are entering every time you wish to use the restroom, but it is a safe gender neutral all gender single stall bathroom that is safe for everyone.

The Academic Success Center's (ASC) Hours are:
Monday - Thursday: 9:00 a.m. - 9:00 p.m.; Friday 9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.

name: Northern Virginia Community College
directions: In the Bisdorf building (AA), on NOVA's Alexandria campus, go to the third floor and stick to the right upon entering the 3rd floor doors. Go into the Women's Center in Room 331. (AA 331) There is a gender neutral all genders bathroom inside. It has one large stall inside and the door can be locked on the door itself, for added privacy, in addition to the stall door lock.
comment: Despite being in the Women's Center, which is gendered in name, anyone of any gender can use this restroom. The Women's Center is also a designated safe space for any time you feel unsafe. You are encouraged to go there if you feel unsafe or just want more privacy. Even if it's just for studying. The name of the Center's room can be misleading, but it is a safe space. The Pride NOVA club meets there as well, so it is absolutely queer safe.
